# Rejection (spec §15): `children :=` is reserved even with NO `{children}`
# placement — the reservation is uniform, it does not depend on whether the slot
# was synthesized. This is what makes the body-scope rule the same for all three
# names.
-- input.gsx --
package views

component Page() {
	{{ children := "hi" }}
	<div>ok</div>
}
-- diagnostics.golden --
4:5: identifier "children" is reserved (the implicit children slot) — rename it
4:5: declared and not used: children
